parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel leak from the carburetor can cause a fire hazard, potentially leading to a vehicle fire, especially when the engine is hot and the fuel is vaporized. This can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the carburetor when restarting the engine after a short period of shutdown
especially in hot weather conditions; fuel sprays out of the carburetor and onto the hot engine and exhaust pipes; the fuel is immediately vaporized; the leak occurs when the engine is hot

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sticking Valves and Engine Performance Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sticking valves can cause the engine to lose power, backfire, cut out, and stall, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded. This issue can also cause the engine to seize, resulting in costly repairs or even engine replacement.
symptoms: especially in low-speed traffic or when idling. The motorcycle may also experience sudden stops on highways
and the engine may seize without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front drive pulley can cause the rear wheel to lock up, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially severe injury or death.
symptoms: oil leak from the transfer case
slight leak near the shaft and drive pulley.
